\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish the deployment mechanics by which authorized changes are packaged,
 tested,
 and moved to production within the Elko County Information Operations Department.
 This policy governs how applications,
 drivers,
 firmware,
 and associated documentation are sourced,
 validated,
 and deployed across all change categories defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 It designates the IOPS Software Repository as the authoritative and exclusive source for all deployment packages,
 establishes the eligibility criteria that govern repository contents,
 and defines the category-specific deployment requirements that apply to Standard,
 Significant,
 and Emergency changes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy is the downstream operational partner of 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Change Management Policy).
 Where 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 governs the authorization decision —
 whether a change may proceed and on what terms —
 this policy governs what happens after that authorization is granted.
\end_layout

