\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure this policy is implemented and enforced across all deployment activity within the Information Operations Department.
 The IT Director shall ensure the IOPS Software Repository is maintained as the exclusive authorized deployment source and that the Department's test environment is established and operational.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure deployment activities comply with this policy across all change categories.
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure the pre-deployment checklist for Emergency deployments is completed and documented before any Emergency deployment proceeds.
 The Assistant IT Director shall oversee post-deployment verification for Significant and Emergency deployments and shall confirm that CI update obligations under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 are fulfilled within the applicable timelines.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Department Personnel
\series default
:
 IT Department personnel authorized with write access to the IOPS Software Repository shall ensure that only items with a corresponding Supported classification under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 are present in the repository.
 All other IT Department personnel shall deploy exclusively from the IOPS Software Repository under all change categories.
 No personnel shall deploy from any source other than the IOPS Software Repository regardless of urgency or authorization status.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All deployment activity within the scope of this policy shall conform to the requirements established herein.
 Deviation from mandatory requirements designated by "shall" or "must" constitutes a policy violation and is subject to enforcement under Policy 5.01.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Exceptions to recommended practices designated by "should" require written approval from the IT Director prior to the deviation.
 The IT Director shall document the rationale and any compensating controls in the relevant change or work order record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
No exception process exists for the IOPS Software Repository requirement.
 Deployment from any source other than the IOPS Software Repository is prohibited under all change categories,
 including Emergency,
 and shall not be authorized by any exception mechanism under this policy or 
\series bold
Policy 
