\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 The IOPS Software Repository
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IOPS Software Repository is the IT-controlled repository designated as the authoritative and exclusive source for all deployment packages within the scope of this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IOPS Software Repository shall be read-only for all personnel except IT Department personnel with authorized write access.
 No personnel shall modify,
 add to,
 or remove items from the repository except through the write-access process established by the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IOPS Software Repository shall not be referred to by server path or share name in this policy or in any policy instrument.
 References shall use the designation "IOPS Software Repository" to preserve policy validity if the repository is relocated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Repository Eligibility
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Only applications,
 drivers,
 firmware,
 and associated documentation corresponding to items with a current Supported classification on the Supported software list maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 shall be present in the IOPS Software Repository and eligible for deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Presence in the repository without a corresponding Supported classification under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 constitutes a policy violation.
 The Assistant IT Director shall remediate any such condition upon discovery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director approval for adding an item to the Supported software list under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 is the intake authorization gate for repository eligibility.
 No separate intake approval process is required under this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Repository Requirement —
 No Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Deployment from any source other than the IOPS Software Repository is prohibited under all change categories,
 including Emergency.
 This requirement applies regardless of urgency,
 authorization status,
 or the identity of the personnel directing the deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Emergency category in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 authorizes expedited change authorization.
 It does not alter,
 waive,
 or supersede the deployment source requirement or the Supported software list eligibility requirement established in this policy.
 An Incident Commander's Emergency designation under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 does not constitute authorization to deploy from an uncontrolled source.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Standard Deployments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A Standard deployment shall be deployed from the IOPS Software Repository per the pre-approved Knowledge Base procedure maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The Knowledge Base procedure is the deployment control for Standard changes;
 no staging or pilot group is required.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The deploying technician shall document the deployment within the associated work order in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The CI update obligation under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 applies upon completion of the deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Post-deployment verification for Standard deployments is implicit in work order closure under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Significant Deployments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A Significant deployment shall be deployed from the IOPS Software Repository.
 Before implementation,
 a deployment package shall be prepared and documented within the RFC record under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Staging or pilot group testing is required prior to full production deployment,
 in accordance with the testing requirements defined in Section 6.7.
 For Significant deployments affecting end-user systems,
 a phased rollout —
 pilot group before full production —
 shall be the default approach where operationally feasible.
 Where a phased rollout is not operationally feasible,
 the deploying technician shall document the basis for that determination in the RFC record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The rollback procedure shall be verified as operational before the deployment proceeds to production.
 All deployment steps shall be documented in the RFC record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Post-deployment verification is required before the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 PIR may be initiated.
 The Assistant IT Director shall confirm that post-deployment verification is complete and documented in the RFC record before the PIR is opened.
 The CI update obligation under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 applies upon completion of the deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Emergency Deployments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
An Emergency deployment shall be deployed from the IOPS Software Repository.
 No exception to this requirement applies under Emergency conditions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Before any Emergency deployment proceeds,
 a pre-deployment checklist shall be completed and documented by the deploying technician.
 The checklist shall confirm each of the following:
 the deployment source is the IOPS Software Repository;
 the package has a corresponding Supported classification under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
;
 and the deploying technician has confirmed the target systems.
 The Assistant IT Director shall verify that the completed checklist is documented in the catch-up RFC record under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Staging is waived for Emergency deployments.
 Post-deployment verification is required before the catch-up RFC record under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 may be closed.
 The 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 PIR serves as the post-deployment review for Emergency deployments;
 no separate deployment review record is required.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The CI update obligation under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 applies under the same twenty-four (24) hour and noon-next-business-day timeline established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Staging and Testing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Information Operations Department shall maintain a dedicated test environment for pre-production validation of Significant deployments.
 The test environment shall consist of one or more virtual machines representative of production system configurations.
 Maintenance of the test environment is a standing operational obligation within the IT Director's operational authority to establish and maintain.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Where the dedicated test environment is not applicable to a specific deployment type —
 for example,
 infrastructure changes that cannot be meaningfully replicated in a virtual machine environment —
 a defined pilot group shall serve as the validation mechanism.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The criteria for test environment applicability and pilot group selection shall be documented in the Knowledge Base under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure that the relevant Knowledge Base entries are current.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8 Post-Deployment Verification and PIR Sequencing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Post-deployment verification is a prerequisite to initiating the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 PIR for Significant and Emergency deployments.
 The PIR shall not be initiated until post-deployment verification confirms that the deployment completed successfully and that no immediate unintended impacts are present.
 The 
